README.md
     1â†’# xxhash
     2â†’
     3â†’[![Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/badge/github.com/cespare/xxhash/v2.svg)](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/cespare/xxhash/v2)
     4â†’[![Test](https://github.com/cespare/xxhash/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/cespare/xxhash/actions/workflows/test.yml)
     5â†’
     6â†’xxhash is a Go implementation of the 64-bit [xxHash] algorithm, XXH64. This is a
     7â†’high-quality hashing algorithm that is much faster than anything in the Go
     8â†’standard library.
     9â†’
    10â†’This package provides a straightforward API:
    11â†’
    12â†’```
    13â†’func Sum64(b []byte) uint64
    14â†’func Sum64String(s string) uint64
    15â†’type Digest struct{ ... }
    16â†’    func New() *Digest
    17â†’```
    18â†’
    19â†’The `Digest` type implements hash.Hash64. Its key methods are:
    20â†’
    21â†’```
    22â†’func (*Digest) Write([]byte) (int, error)
    23â†’func (*Digest) WriteString(string) (int, error)
    24â†’func (*Digest) Sum64() uint64
    25â†’```
    26â†’
    27â†’The package is written with optimized pure Go and also contains even faster
    28â†’assembly implementations for amd64 and arm64. If desired, the `purego` build tag
    29â†’opts into using the Go code even on those architectures.
    30â†’
    31â†’[xxHash]: https://xxhash.com/
    32â†’
    33â†’## Compatibility
    34â†’
    35â†’This package is in a module and the latest code is in version 2 of the module.
    36â†’You need a version of Go with at least "minimal module compatibility" to use
    37â†’github.com/cespare/xxhash/v2:
    38â†’
    39â†’* 1.9.7+ for Go 1.9
    40â†’* 1.10.3+ for Go 1.10
    41â†’* Go 1.11 or later
    42â†’
    43â†’I recommend using the latest release of Go.
    44â†’
    45â†’## Benchmarks
    46â†’
    47â†’Here are some quick benchmarks comparing the pure-Go and assembly
    48â†’implementations of Sum64.
    49â†’
    50â†’| input size | purego    | asm       |
    51â†’| ---------- | --------- | --------- |
    52â†’| 4 B        |  1.3 GB/s |  1.2 GB/s |
    53â†’| 16 B       |  2.9 GB/s |  3.5 GB/s |
    54â†’| 100 B      |  6.9 GB/s |  8.1 GB/s |
    55â†’| 4 KB       | 11.7 GB/s | 16.7 GB/s |
    56â†’| 10 MB      | 12.0 GB/s | 17.3 GB/s |
    57â†’
    58â†’These numbers were generated on Ubuntu 20.04 with an Intel Xeon Platinum 8252C
    59â†’CPU using the following commands under Go 1.19.2:
    60â†’
    61â†’```
    62â†’benchstat <(go test -tags purego -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    63â†’benchstat <(go test -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    64â†’```
    65â†’
    66â†’## Projects using this package
    67â†’
    68â†’- [InfluxDB](https://github.com/influxdata/influxdb)
    69â†’- [Prometheus](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus)
    70â†’- [VictoriaMetrics](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/VictoriaMetrics)
    71â†’- [FreeCache](https://github.com/coocood/freecache)
    72â†’- [FastCache](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/fastcache)
    73â†’- [Ristretto](https://github.com/dgraph-io/ristretto)
    74â†’- [Badger](https://github.com/dgraph-io/badger)
